The paper deals with the problem of localization and mapping for autonomous vehicles, which is a core topic in robotics (cs.RO). The proposed approach involves the use of deep learning for object segmentation from 3D LiDAR point clouds, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of odometry and mapping algorithms, which are common in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL) research. However, since the focus is on robotics and computer vision, cs.RO and cs.CV are the most likely categories.
